      "content": "It's not a good idea to take multiple pain relievers like ibuprofen and aspirin at the same time, as this can increase the risk of serious side effects. Make sure to rest and avoid putting strain on your back. However, taking an additional dosage of ibuprofen after the current dose wears off may not be necessary, as you've already taken a total of 1600mg for the day without relief. Consider physical therapy advice for proper back care, and potentially consult your doctor for personalized advice. It's also important to be careful, as excessive ibuprofen use can negatively affect your kidneys and other organs over time. Avoid using these medications if there's no immediate need for pain relief. Safe sleep and proper rest are key. Some recommended sleep remedies include raised leg positioning, topical muscle relaxants, and engaging in light stretching or yoga. Be sure to check with your healthcare provider for personalized recommendations in the future.",
